gartigen poeta doctus präziser zu bestimmen.  aThe studies collected in this volume examine previously undervalued and undiscovered aspects of Rist's multi-facetted oeuvre. In a series of essays, renowned authors from the fields of literary and music history, church history, and the history of science and hymnology assess Rist's role as a communicator while revealing the heterogeneity of his creative work and the wide range of his influence.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4a17. Jahrhundert. 4aBarockzeit. 4aFrömmigkeitsgeschichte. 4aIntermedialität. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  a17th century.  aBaroque period.  afaith history.  aintermediality.1 aArend, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker-Cantarino, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenthien, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBetz, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDammann, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarber, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrosse, Sven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeintzsch, Sabrina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirschmann, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuck, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngen, Ferdinand van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJahn, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJahn, Bernhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKadelbach, Ada, e